<TEXT>
a hispanic police officer convicted in the deaths 
of two black men that touched off rioting last year was rushed to a 
hospital tuesday night after a reported suicide attempt police 
said 
william lozano 30 was taken to the emergency room of coral 
reef hospital around 705 pm said hospital president kenneth 
sample lozano was in stable condition late tuesday but hospital 
officials refused to release any details on his condition 
the emergency call initially came in to police as an attempted 
suicide said metrodade police spokeswoman myriam royle 
when police and rescue units reached lozanos home in 
southwestern dade county they found lozano awake and conscious 
it was unclear what was wrong with lozano or if he had taken 
some kind of pills ms royle said 
the officers mother haydee lozano brother jairo lozano also 
a miami police officer and former partner dawn campbell were at 
the hospital south of miami 
lozano shot an unarmed motorcyclist to death on jan 16 1989 
and the bikers passenger died in the resulting crash the deaths 
touched off three days of rioting in miamis black neighborhoods 
that resulted in one death 11 injuries and hundreds of arrests it 
was the fourth round of racial unrest in miami in the 1980s all 
touched off by the slayings of blacks by white officers or the 
acquittal of those officers 
the colombianborn officer who was suspended without pay from 
the miami police department was convicted of manslaughter dec 7 
and sentenced to seven years in state prison in january he 
appealed the conviction and has been free on bond 
