a bus carrying a high school track team 
rearended a truck tuesday night sending 42 people to hospitals 
officials said 
the accident on us 231 in this southeastern alabama town 
apparently occurred after the trailer separated from the trucks 
cab and its brake lights went out said police chief virgil dobbs 
the bus driver couldnt see the trailer and crashed into it 
the bus driver the truck driver and all 40 students aboard the 
bus were taken to three hospitals some were taken by helicopter 
from fort rucker army base in dothan 14 miles to the south 
all the injured were treated for such injuries as whiplash 
bruises and scratches and released said dothan schools 
superintendent gene watson 
we were very fortunate that there were no serious injuries 
watson said 
the bus was carrying members of the dothan high school track 
team home from a track meet police said 
watson said assistant track coach edward fleming who was 
driving the bus deserved praise for avoiding a 40foot ravine at 
the side of the road 
