targeted at hate groups such as the klan 
the law is not vague it says do not wear a mask unless you 
fall within one of the exceptions said david m fuller chief 
assistant solicitor for gwinnett county who will represent the 
state at the hearing 
the law makes it a misdemeanor punishable by up to a year in 
jail and a 1000 fine to wear a hood or a mask to conceal ones 
identity when on public property exceptions include holiday 
costumes on the day of the holiday masks for use in sports 
theatrical garb or gas masks 
it does not violate free speech because it is in the pursuit 
of a legitimate public interest which is to keep the public free 
from threats and intimidation fuller said 
superior court senior judge osgood williams who as a legislator 
helped write the mask law said its always been my feeling that 
the bill in a large measure brought about the demise of the ku 
klux klan as a potent force it still should be the law of the 
land 
