of the mask is to conceal the klan member and the only purpose of 
concealing the member in public has to do with worry over law 
enforcement finding out about who is committing crimes 
zeskind said the klans reason for launching this challenge may 
have less to do with regaining the right to wear a mask than 
inspiring its membership 
he said klan groups have suffered several setbacks in georgia 
courts over the past couple of years and this may be an attempt 
to rally the troops around some legal effort this may be an 
internal thing 
fuller said virtually every state has an antimask law though a 
few including those in california tennessee and massachusetts 
have been struck down 
but he said he believed georgias law was more narrowly written 
than those that were ruled unconstitutional 
