said american farmers and the us economy benefit from the recent 
upswing in tobacco exports 
kleckner in a statement said that increased sales of tobacco 
leaf and products are a result of american farmers producing they 
type of product wanted by foreign customers he also cited the 
removal of overseas trade barriers primarily in japan taiwan and 
south korea 
