countries have not previously been eligible for the subsidized 
flour sales under the export enhancement program or eep three 
countries benin central african republic and zaire had 
participated before 
the 16 newcomers are angola burundi cameroon congo gabon 
ghana guinea liberia mali mauritania niger rwanda sierre 
leone tanzania togo and zambia 
sales of wheat flour will be made to buyers in these 19 
countries at competitive world prices the announcement said the 
sales will be made through regular commercial channels by private 
exporting companies 
a metric tons is about 2205 pounds 
the eep arrangement allows private exporters to sell wheat 
flour and other designated commodities to specified countries at 
reduced prices in order to meet foreign competition 
exporters then collect free government surpluses of grain or 
other products as bonuses or subsidies to make up for the reduced 
prices 
