the long road to a seat in a freely 
elected hungarian parliament was rutted with prison the threat of 
the gallows and selfexile for bela kiraly who led freedom 
fighters against soviet tanks in 1956 
for the 78yearold kiraly victory at the polls on april 8 
capped a perilous journey that saw him change continents and 
professions three times 
the ramrod career army officer fled after the failed 1956 revolt 
and began a new life in the united states as a history professor 
he returned last year to help cement democracy in his homeland and 
plans to sell his home in highland lakes nj 
