superior court judge sandra hamlin on tuesday had ordered jury 
selection closed on the grounds publicity would have a chilling 
effect on prospective jurors 
but supreme court associate justice neil l lynch overruled him 
on a challenge by the boston globe 
david and ginger twitchell are charged with manslaughter for 
relying on faith instead of medicine to heal their 2yearold son 
robyn who died in 1986 of a bowel obstruction 
prosecutors argued that the childs life could have been saved 
if he had received conventional medical treatment 
defense attorney rikki klieman contended that the twitchells 
far from acting recklessly sought the only real cure dictated by 
their beliefs 
founded in 1879 by mary baker eddy the church of christ 
science believes that disease like sin can be healed by 
spiritual means alone the case is being closely watched by the 
church which contends its doctrine is under attack 
the us supreme court typically has refused to hear such cases 
