the westerly ri sun on doublehulled tankers 
conoco inc a houstonbased oil company in one bold stroke is 
proving the truth of two old adages we can learn from our 
mistakes and an ounce of prevention is worth a pound of cure 
conoco is ordering two new oil tankers but unlike the 
singlehulled exxon valdez which after running aground dumped 11 
million gallons of petroleum into alaskan waters last year these 
new ships will have double hulls 
the folks at conoco are well aware that this type of 
construction will increase the cost of their new seagoing 
acquisitions by as much as 15 percent somewhere into the 70 
million to 90 million range 
but they are also aware that a coast guard study has found that 
if the exxon valdez had been of doublehull construction its 
petroleum loss after running aground would have been reduced by as 
much as 60 percent 
truly conoco has learned from exxons experience and with what 
has been learned is making a powerful statement that at sea and on 
land it is better to prevent oil spills than clean up after them 
