constitution brokered by the british that contained entrenched 
racial provisions protecting the interests of the 90000strong 
white community 
we shall proceed in the name of justice equity and fairness 
to amend these provisions so as to make more land available to the 
peasant population he said 
under the socalled lancaster house constitution 20 seats in 
the 100member parliament were reserved for whites for the first 
seven years of independence legal clauses blocked the seizure of 
whiteowned property 
the formula was intended to stop a mass exodus of skilled whites 
the government says 4000 mostly white commercial farmers still 
own more than onefourth of all land while some 8 million peasants 
occupy about onethird of property the rest is state property and 
wilderness preserves 
but state officials have said that after april 18 they will 
move to buy littleused farmland widescale seizures of farms are 
not expected 
during his anniversary address mugabe acknowledged the role of 
large commercial farms in the economy he said that apart from 
wheat imports this southern african nation of 92 million people 
is selfsufficient in food 
he also praised local industries mainly in the hands of white 
entrepreneurs manufacturers generate nearly 30 percent of the 
gross domestic product of about 4 billion mugabe said 
he said more local and foreign investment in production was 
needed to combat rising uemployment and shortages of essential 
commodities 
flanked by president danial arap moi of kenya and president 
hastings kamuzu banda of malawi mugabe said his people were eager 
for regional peace and an end to south africas system of racial 
separation 
mugabe and moi are mediating efforts to end the 12yearold 
civil war in neighboring mozambique 
hundreds of zimbabweans have died in crossborder raids by 
