on the 84th anniversary of the great quake 
folks who live in the earthchurning san francisco region had 
plenty reason to pay close attention to the pulse of the san 
andreas fault 
they got a chilling reminder when a series of earthquakes 
rumbled through northern california on wednesday shattering nerves 
but little else 
the tremors along the san andreas hit about 90 minutes after 150 
survivors of the 1906 quake and subsequent inferno gathered in the 
predawn darkness to talk about the time the earth shook and the sky 
glowed 
the group has held a reunion every year since 1924 at lottas 
fountain on market street where they observe a moment of silence 
at 513 am when the estimated 83magnitude quake struck on 
april 18 1906 
some survivors were just a few days old 84 years ago others 
were old enough to remember camping in city parks while fires raged 
throughout the city 
one man recalled how he was tossed from the first floor window 
of the orphanage he lived in as the children were evacuated 
