paint gold a fire hydrant that continued to work after the 1906 
quake and helped save a neighborhood 
one or two of the survivors commented that it didnt faze them 
at all as they had experienced the big one said sapienza 
the great quake killed hundreds perhaps thousands destroyed 
about 30000 buildings and left 225000 homeless 
about 400000 square miles were believed rattled when a 270mile 
zone of the 650mile fault slipped in a titanic shrug of the 
plates that separate the north american continent from the pacific 
basin the western side of the rupture moved north while the 
eastern side moved south 
one geologist said it was as though san francisco and los 
angeles were being drawn closer together 
for decades it was believed that about 700 people died in the 
quake but in recent years research by san francisco city 
archivist gladys hansen documented at least 2500 deaths and she 
indicated the real toll may be much higher 
mrs hansen reached her conclusions by examining public records 
obituaries and clippings from old newspapers and letters from 
people telling her of relatives who died she found many quake 
victims died in other cities after an estimated 250000 people 
evacuated san francisco on boats and trains within three days of 
the catastrophe 
nearly every city from eureka near the oregon line south to 
salinas near monterey sustained damage 
