of an electrically powered car in recognition of consumer demand 
for a cleaner environment chairman roger b smith said wednesday 
the nations largest automaker intends to be the first to 
massmarket the vehicle smith said in a speech to the national 
press club gm unveiled a prototype vehicle the impact in january 
he refused to say when or where the car would be built or to 
reveal technical information about the vehicle saying he did not 
want to tip off competitors in the 1970s gm announced it would 
produce a 1985model electric car but it dropped that project long 
before production 
smith said the goal is to manufacture a car that would match 
todays safety and performance standards without the air pollution 
of an internal combustion engine generation of the electricity of 
course would create other pollution if fossil fuels were used in 
the power plant 
