midwest as the mercury dipped below freezing breaking 
lowtemperature records in five cities and tying them in four 
scattered snow showers fell over central new england 
showers and occasional thunderstorms were scattered from central 
arkansas to oklahoma the texas panhandle the northwest third of 
texas southern and western new mexico southern colorado arizona 
and southern nevada small hail fell near monte vista colo and 
at truth or consequences nm 
a cold front accompanied by northerly winds made temperatures 
plunge in much of the eastern half of the nation overnight before 
moving into the gulf of mexico 
it was 22 degrees in flint mich where the old mark of 23 had 
stood since 1953 and 31 degrees in atlantic city nj 32 
degrees 1983 other records were fort wayne ind 23 degrees 27 
in 1926 and 1953 mansfield ohio 23 26 in 1983 and south bend 
ind 24 25 in 1983 
records were tied in binghamton ny 28 degrees 1962 
evansville ind 31 1983 moline ill 23 1983 and rockford 
ill 22 1983 
temperatures around the nation at 3 pm edt ranged from 32 
degrees at limestone maine to 91 degrees at fort meyers fla 
the low temperature for the lower 48 states was 16 degrees in 
pellston mich 
