<TEXT>
britain said wednesday it is convinced that iraq 
was trying to build a giant gun but that customs officers 
frustrated the project by seizing eight steel tubes last week 
let me make it absolutely clear that the gun itself cannot be 
in operation without all its parts and it is a great success on 
the behalf of this country to have been able to prevent that 
happening trade and industry secretary nicholas ridley told the 
house of commons 
weapons experts have said a gun on the scale of the seized parts 
131 feet long with a bore of 39 inches would have the potential 
to lob nuclear or chemical warheads hundreds of miles or even 
boost rockets into orbit 
the iraqi government and the manufacturer sheffield 
forgemasters have insisted the tubes were designed for a 
petrochemical plant 
the iraqi embassy in london and forgemasters said they had no 
comment on the governments statement wednesday 
ridley said the government believed that iraqs gun project 
followed the designs of gerald bull a canadianborn us 
ballistics expert who was murdered in brussels on march 22 
the financial times reported wednesday that the british and 
belgian governments have evidence that a belgian defense company 
prb was contracted by iraq to help produce a boosterassisted 
shell for the same type of gun prb is owned by the british 
munitions company astra holdings 
astra holdings issued a statement wednesday night saying that 
after it acquired prb last sept 11 it discovered a contract for 
unusual types of gun propellant for very large guns 
although all normal export documentation was in place and 
appeared correct astra immediately reported the matter to her 
majestys government the contract is no longer in force the 
statement said 
astra holdings did not say whether the propellant had been 
shipped to iraq 
ridley confirmed that his own department had cleared the 
production of the tubes two years ago but said his agency had no 
knowledge the goods were designed to form part of a gun until a 
few days ago 
the government is entirely satisfied that these tubes form 
part of a gun and that the customs action was correct he said 
ridleys statement was the first cabinetlevel statement that 
the tubing had military potential 
during her visit to bermuda to meet with president bush last 
weekend prime minister margaret thatcher said more information was 
needed to determine the purpose of the tubes 
gordon brown of the opposition labor party contended the 
government had been deceived and duped on a grand scale 
this government allowed through an order which could have made 
it possible for iraq to operate a weapon whose use could affect 
regional and even world stability brown said 
the customs and excise office seized the tubes on the docks at 
middlesbrough last thursday after a ministry of defense expert 
concluded they could be used as a gun barrel 
sheffield forgemasters said it had already shipped 44 sections 
of tubing to iraq 
but ridley said wednesday i understand that it will not be 
possible to build a complete fullsize gun from parts that have 
been supplied from britain 
ridley said his department was contacted in 1988 by sheffield 
forgemasters asking whether licenses were required for export of 
tubes to iraq for use in the polymerization of polyethylene 
the department was also contacted by walter somers ltd of 
birmingham about a separate order of metal tubes from bulls 
belgian company space research corp 
ridley said the export licenses wouldnt have been granted if 
his department had known at the time that the tubes were designed 
for use in a giant gun 
britain banned arms shipments to iran and iraq when the two 
countries were at war and the ban remains in effect 
western fears abut iraqi arms programs have intensified in 
recent weeks on march 28 british customs officials seized 
usmade parts for atomic bomb triggers that were bound for iraq 
iraq has denied seeking a nuclear capability but has confirmed 
its arsenal includes chemical weapons 
iraqi president saddam hussein recently threatened to use 
missiles armed with chemical weapons against israel if israeli 
forces attacked his country 
