ms brooks would like to live in a quiet safe neighborhood but 
a plan to demolish the 388unit housing project and relocate its 
residents has stirred controversy in this largely middleclass city 
of 350000 along the missouri river 
the omaha housing authority wants to use a 9 million us 
housing and urban development grant to scatter 194 of the families 
at logan fontenelle around the city a plan rejected 43 by the 
city council in december some opponents said it was too costly 
others wanted more say in where the new housing units would be 
located 
the housing authority then revised the plan so that it didnt 
need city council approval for the scattered site housing but the 
council still must approve the razing of the logan fontenelle a 
