<TEXT>
spunk is an apt title for george c wolfes 
stage adaptation of three short stories by zora neale hurston 
the playlets which opened wednesday at offbroadways new york 
shakespeare festival are gutsy gritty and often very funny 
examinations of black life both in the south and up north during 
the 1920s 
wolfe author of that satiric look at black history called the 
colored museum uses song mime dance and story theater 
techniques to make hurstons stories come alive under his 
direction they have made the leap from page to stage with an 
irresistible theatricality 
the first play sweat is a familiar tale of a woman done 
wrong by her man delia a religious hardworking laundress is 
increasingly battered by her philandering husband her revenge is 
positively serpentine danitra vance personifies the womans 
sweetness while reggie montgomery portrays her doomed helpmate 
with a stylish sense of evil 
style also carries story in harlem slang an uproarious 
confrontation between two harlem dandies who work hard at doing 
nothing at all if their dialogue is often incomprehensible the 
meaning is very clear as they attempt to cadge free meals from 
passing women montgomery and k todd freeman play the preening 
roosters who dont miss a word or a beat as they strut their stuff 
and the theater program contains a glossary of the more arcane 
terms for audiences who have to know every word 
the longest play the gilded sixbits forms the second half 
of the evening it meanders a bit and the story it tells is also 
one of love betrayed but this time the victim is a husband whose 
wife falls for a wealthier man and unlike the curtainraiser 
the gilded sixbits is a plea for forgiveness that succeeds 
the three sories are punctuated by some wonderful music mostly 
blues written and performed by the oddly named chic street man he 
is assisted by ann duquesnay a woman who can sing and sashay with 
the best of them 
hurstons stories are testaments to the human spirit her people 
are more than just survivors they thrive in adversity in 
spunk wolfe has managed to document the way they flourish with 
grace good humor and affection 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

