about 11000 customers in the watsonville and santa cruz area lost 
power all service was restored by noon 
wednesday marked the 84th anniversary of the 1906 quake which 
struck at 513 am on april 18 although the richter scale didnt 
exist then it was later determined that the quakes magnitude was 
83 
