james henry parker arrived in the rolling brittle woodlands of 
the texas hill country in the early 1870s accompanied by his young 
bride matilda a grandniece of davy crockett a name as famous as 
the alamo itself 
soon the couples original 160acre tract grew to 12000 acres 
and jim and tildy produced 11 children including a son named jess 
who in 1913 married lorena milam a relative of ben milam another 
history book hero 
in the late 1930s jess called big daddy and lorena big 
mama moved into the remote family homesite now known as old 
ranch and raised five children 
