bank of new england corp says it plans to make 
the company smaller but stronger by stripping its troubled real 
estate loans from its main banking business 
the strategy unveiled tuesday will create a separate 
collecting bank to deal with a mountain of troubled loans and 
use advertising to allay depositor fears 
the plan also calls for the bank to sell its rhode island and 
maine subsidiaries and eventually cut its assets to about 20 
billion assets currently stand at 25 billion and were 32 billion 
just last fall 
solving the banks problems will require major financial and 
business restructuring which while challenging will allow us to 
rebuild a strong regional bank chairman lawrence fish said 
fish who succeeded ousted chairman walter j connolly last 
month said the company will focus on businesses including retail 
and commercial banking and real estate lending 
were going to keep it simple fish said in a statement 
were going to take deposits and were going to make sound 
loans 
the bank which has been operating under government orders for 
more than a month lost more than 1 billion last year it recently 
announced plans to cut 5600 workers or onethird of the payroll 
through a combination of layoffs attrition and the sale of assets 
much of the banks trouble has been blamed on shaky construction 
loans that were exposed during a downturn in the northeast real 
estate market but analysts warn that the bank could face more 
trouble as the new england economy continues to worsen 
deteriorating the banks assets further 
some analysts had suggested that the bank separate the bad loans 
from the rest of the assets in order to alleviate the burden from 
the solid operations 
the bank said steven e wheeler a former morgan stanley 
executive would serve as executive vice president and oversee the 
new collecting bank 
this operation will restructure the troubled real estate assets 
and possibly offer them for sale the bank said wheeler has 
experience in the new england real estate market having served as 
president of first winthrop corp a bostonbased real estate 
syndication and investment firm 
the bank also is trying to improve its capital levels and reduce 
borrowings from the federal reserve bank part of the plan is to 
use advertising campaigns to stem the fears of depositors who have 
pulled billions of dollars from the company 
bank of new england said it would adopt a new organizational 
structure that would change management processes and emphasize 
accountability 
as part of its sale of assets the bank also announced tuesday 
