depressed in the next few weeks 
opec officials had been expecting prices to decline in the 
apriljune period when demand for oil normally weakens with warmer 
temperatures in the united states and other consuming nations but 
last weeks sudden fall was a surprise 
in their statement saudi arabias hisham nazer kuwaits ali 
khalifa alsabah and the emirates mana saeed otaiba expressed 
grave concern about the recent developments in the market 
they blamed the fall in prices on increased crude production by 
both opec and nonopec countries 
the solution which would guarantee relative market stability 
is for opec members to commit themselves to respect the production 
ceiling and the individual production quotas set out for the member 
states according to the statement carried by the saudi press 
agency 
